1
00:00:07,625 --> 00:00:10,294
Hey, Eddie.

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:14,799
- What are you doing here?
- Watching you sleep.

3
00:00:15,341 --> 00:00:16,300
Why?

4
00:00:16,551 --> 00:00:19,178
It makes me feel peaceful.

5
00:00:19,429 --> 00:00:20,847
Please.

6
00:00:21,097 --> 00:00:22,306
I can't sleep now!

7
00:00:22,557 --> 00:00:25,309
You want me to sing?

8
00:00:26,561 --> 00:00:29,856
That's it. I want you
out of the apartment now!

9
00:00:30,106 --> 00:00:32,025
What are you talking about?

10
00:00:32,275 --> 00:00:35,236
Hannibal Lecter?

11
00:00:35,445 --> 00:00:37,572
Better roommate than you.

12
00:00:37,822 --> 00:00:41,659
I don't think you're being fair!
One night you see me and you get scared.

13
00:00:41,909 --> 00:00:45,621
What about the other nights
when you don't see me?

14
00:00:45,872 --> 00:00:47,832
Last night you went
and got some water...

15
00:00:48,082 --> 00:00:51,669
...and I was nice enough
to hide behind the door.

16
00:00:51,919 --> 00:00:55,006
I didn't realize that.

17
00:00:55,256 --> 00:00:57,175
Get out now!

18
00:00:57,425 --> 00:00:59,052
You really want me out?

19
00:00:59,302 --> 00:01:00,261
Yes, please.

20
00:01:00,511 --> 00:01:03,264
Then I want to hear you say
you want me out.

21
00:01:03,514 --> 00:01:04,599
I want you out.

22
00:01:04,849 --> 00:01:08,061
I want to hear it from your lips.

23
00:01:08,061 --> 00:01:09,354
Where'd you hear it before?

24
00:01:09,604 --> 00:01:12,690
All right. You know what?
Consider me gone.

25
00:01:12,972 --> 00:01:14,878
You know what I'll do? I'll go
move into my brother's basement.

26
00:01:14,928 --> 00:01:17,909
When he finds out,
I'll go find some place else.

27
00:01:18,340 --> 00:01:23,137
I'll be out by the time
you get home from work tomorrow.

28
00:01:23,137 --> 00:01:26,682
- <i>Thank you.</i>
- I heard that.

29
00:01:27,099 --> 00:01:30,227
The One Where Eddie Won't Go

30
00:02:18,428 --> 00:02:20,221
Well, look at you!

31
00:02:20,471 --> 00:02:23,600
Finally got that
time machine working, huh?

32
00:02:23,850 --> 00:02:24,726
You like it?

33
00:02:24,976 --> 00:02:27,770
This guy was selling them
on 8th Avenue and I thought...

34
00:02:28,021 --> 00:02:29,022
..."You know what I don't have?"

35
00:02:29,272 --> 00:02:31,733
A mirror?

36
00:02:31,983 --> 00:02:35,945
Fine, make fun.
I think it's jaunty.

37
00:02:36,195 --> 00:02:39,574
For a guy who's recently lost his job,
you're in a good mood.

38
00:02:39,824 --> 00:02:42,994
I'll be all right.
I'm not starting from square one.

39
00:02:43,244 --> 00:02:47,332
I was Dr. Drake Ramoray
on <i>Days of our Lives</i>.

40
00:02:47,582 --> 00:02:50,710
That's got to have some kind of cachet.

41
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:52,879
Cachet? Jaunty?

42
00:02:53,129 --> 00:02:57,342
Chandler gave me
word-of-the-day toilet paper.

43
00:02:57,842 --> 00:03:00,887
I'm gonna get some coffee.

44
00:03:02,515 --> 00:03:05,006
Go on. You know you want to.

45
00:03:11,711 --> 00:03:13,373
- No?
- No.

46
00:03:16,413 --> 00:03:18,249
So? Did you read the book?

47
00:03:18,499 --> 00:03:20,626
Oh, my God.
It was incredible!

48
00:03:20,876 --> 00:03:23,129
Didn't it, like,
totally speak to you?

49
00:03:23,379 --> 00:03:24,421
What book is this?

50
00:03:24,672 --> 00:03:29,093
You have to read this book.
It's called <i>Be Your Own Wind Keeper</i>.

51
00:03:29,343 --> 00:03:31,512
It's about how women need
to become more empowered.

52
00:03:31,762 --> 00:03:35,808
But there's wind.

53
00:03:35,975 --> 00:03:38,686
And the wind can make us goddesses.

54
00:03:38,936 --> 00:03:44,191
Do you know who takes our wind?
Men. They just take it.

55
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,569
Men just take our wind?

56
00:03:46,819 --> 00:03:51,907
All the time. Because they
are the lightning-bearers.

57
00:03:53,534 --> 00:03:56,871
That sounds kind of cool.
It's like <i>The Hobbit</i>.

58
00:03:57,121 --> 00:03:59,748
It is nothing like <i>The Hobbit</i>.

59
00:03:59,999 --> 00:04:02,585
It's like reading about
every relationship I've ever had.

60
00:04:02,835 --> 00:04:03,961
Except for Richard.

61
00:04:04,211 --> 00:04:07,715
Richard would never steal your wind.

62
00:04:07,965 --> 00:04:10,426
Because he's yummy.

63
00:04:10,676 --> 00:04:11,677
But all the others.

64
00:04:11,927 --> 00:04:14,764
And the part about how
they're always drinking...

65
00:04:15,014 --> 00:04:16,891
...from our pool of inner power.

66
00:04:17,141 --> 00:04:19,351
But God forbid we should take a sip.

67
00:04:19,602 --> 00:04:21,687
Anybody want a cruller?

68
00:04:21,937 --> 00:04:24,440
This is a typical
lightning-bearer thing.

69
00:04:24,690 --> 00:04:26,108
It's like...

70
00:04:26,358 --> 00:04:31,572
..."Hello. Who wants one of
my phallic-shaped man-cakes?"

71
00:04:37,489 --> 00:04:38,757
Who've you been dating?

72
00:04:46,203 --> 00:04:50,791
Don't worry about it, already!
Things happen.

73
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:55,254
You're not mad at me
for getting fired and everything?

74
00:04:55,504 --> 00:04:57,089
Look at me.

75
00:04:57,339 --> 00:05:00,342
Look at me!

76
00:05:00,676 --> 00:05:04,638
Do I have lipstick on my teeth?

77
00:05:07,308 --> 00:05:08,475
Can we get back to me?

78
00:05:08,726 --> 00:05:12,938
Look, honey. People get fired
left and right in this business.

79
00:05:13,188 --> 00:05:16,233
I already got you an audition
for <i>Another World</i>.

80
00:05:16,483 --> 00:05:18,444
All right!

81
00:05:18,694 --> 00:05:20,571
"Cab Driver Number 2"?

82
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:23,741
You're welcome.

83
00:05:24,408 --> 00:05:26,493
But I was Dr. Drake Ramoray!

84
00:05:26,744 --> 00:05:30,205
How can I go from being
a neurosurgeon to driving a cab?

85
00:05:30,206 --> 00:05:35,776
Hey. There was a time when I used to
play Pickle Tickle with Rick Harrison.

86
00:05:37,556 --> 00:05:40,851
Things change. Roll with them.

87
00:05:41,101 --> 00:05:43,270
But this is a two-line part!

88
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:45,605
It's like taking a step backwards.

89
00:05:45,856 --> 00:05:49,276
I'm not gonna do this.

90
00:05:50,944 --> 00:05:53,905
I'm gonna tell you the same thing
I told Al Minza...

91
00:05:54,156 --> 00:05:57,409
...and his pyramid of dogs.

92
00:05:57,659 --> 00:06:02,622
Take any job you can get,
and don't make on the floor.

93
00:06:02,998 --> 00:06:05,000
I'm sorry.

94
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:08,003
I'll see you.

95
00:06:09,004 --> 00:06:10,339
God!

96
00:06:10,589 --> 00:06:12,674
Oh, God!
I mean, it's just so...

97
00:06:12,924 --> 00:06:14,760
Isn't it?

98
00:06:15,010 --> 00:06:17,471
This is like reading
about my own life!

99
00:06:17,721 --> 00:06:22,184
This book could have been called
<i>Be Your Own Wind Keeper, Rachel</i>!

100
00:06:22,434 --> 00:06:24,311
It wouldn't have sold
a million copies...

101
00:06:24,561 --> 00:06:28,273
...but it would've made
a nice gift for you.

102
00:06:29,399 --> 00:06:33,070
Sweetie, we've got to go.

103
00:06:36,156 --> 00:06:40,953
No! Why do we always have to do
everything according to your timetable?

104
00:06:41,203 --> 00:06:44,998
Actually, it's the movie theater
that has the timetable.

105
00:06:45,248 --> 00:06:48,418
It's so you don't miss the beginning.

106
00:06:48,669 --> 00:06:55,133
This isn't about the movie theater.
This is about you stealing my wind.

107
00:06:55,676 --> 00:06:58,804
You go, girl!

108
00:07:00,180 --> 00:07:03,934
I can't pull that off, can I?

109
00:07:04,184 --> 00:07:07,104
Excuse me, your wind?

110
00:07:07,354 --> 00:07:08,814
Yes, my wind.

111
00:07:09,064 --> 00:07:14,152
How do you expect me to grow
if you won't let me blow?

112
00:07:19,116 --> 00:07:22,703
You know I don't...

113
00:07:23,745 --> 00:07:27,499
...have a problem with that.

114
00:07:36,842 --> 00:07:41,763
I just really need to be
with myself right now.

115
00:07:42,014 --> 00:07:43,849
I'm sorry.

116
00:07:44,099 --> 00:07:47,603
You're right.
I don't have to apologize.

117
00:07:47,853 --> 00:07:50,981
Sorry. Damn it!

118
00:07:56,111 --> 00:07:57,696
- What is it?
- I don't know.

119
00:07:57,946 --> 00:08:00,657
It's got all this stuff
about wind and trees...

120
00:08:00,908 --> 00:08:02,492
...and some sacred pool.

121
00:08:02,743 --> 00:08:05,913
I don't really get it.
But she's pretty upset about it.

122
00:08:06,163 --> 00:08:10,500
This is why I don't date
women who read.

123
00:08:11,919 --> 00:08:13,837
What's that?

124
00:08:14,087 --> 00:08:15,589
It's my VIS A bill.

125
00:08:15,839 --> 00:08:19,635
Envelope one of two.

126
00:08:20,218 --> 00:08:24,514
- That can't be good.
- Open it, open it.

127
00:08:26,225 --> 00:08:28,185
Oh, my God!

128
00:08:28,435 --> 00:08:31,813
Look at this!
How did I spend so much money?

129
00:08:32,064 --> 00:08:36,401
That's just the minimum amount.
That's your total.

130
00:08:37,444 --> 00:08:41,448
Thirty-five hundred dollars
at "Porcelain Safari"?

131
00:08:41,698 --> 00:08:44,034
My animals.

132
00:08:44,284 --> 00:08:49,331
The guy said they suited me. He spoke
with an accent. I was confused.

133
00:08:49,581 --> 00:08:50,916
I don't know what to do!

134
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:54,086
You can start by driving a cab
on <i>Another World</i>.

135
00:08:54,336 --> 00:08:56,046
- What?
- That audition?

136
00:08:56,296 --> 00:08:58,048
That's a two-line part!

137
00:08:58,298 --> 00:09:02,427
Joey, you owe $1100
at "I Love Lucite."

138
00:09:02,678 --> 00:09:04,805
- So what?
- So suck it up, man.

139
00:09:05,055 --> 00:09:06,723
It's a job. It's money.

140
00:09:06,974 --> 00:09:11,603
I don't need you getting judgmental
and condescending and pedantic.

141
00:09:11,853 --> 00:09:14,731
Toilet paper?

142
00:09:16,233 --> 00:09:19,069
I'm not being any of those things.
I'm being realistic.

143
00:09:19,319 --> 00:09:21,113
You're supposed to be my friend!

144
00:09:21,363 --> 00:09:22,197
I am your friend.

145
00:09:22,447 --> 00:09:24,491
Then tell me things like,
"You'll be fine."

146
00:09:24,741 --> 00:09:27,828
And "Something big's gonna
come along. I know it!"

147
00:09:28,078 --> 00:09:29,371
But I don't know it.

148
00:09:29,621 --> 00:09:34,668
What I do know is you owe $2300
at "Isn't It Chromantic?"

149
00:09:34,668 --> 00:09:36,420
I'm aware of what I owe.

150
00:09:36,670 --> 00:09:40,465
Then get some sense.
It took you 10 years to get that job.

151
00:09:40,716 --> 00:09:43,510
- How long till you get another?
- I don't want to hear this!

152
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:44,803
I'm just saying...

153
00:09:45,053 --> 00:09:48,724
Well, don't "just say"!

154
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:52,561
Maybe I should just go.

155
00:09:54,062 --> 00:09:56,732
I'll see you later.

156
00:09:56,982 --> 00:09:58,525
Just think about it.

157
00:09:58,775 --> 00:10:00,611
I don't need to think about it!

158
00:10:00,861 --> 00:10:03,071
I was Dr. Drake Ramoray!

159
00:10:03,322 --> 00:10:05,157
That was huge!

160
00:10:05,407 --> 00:10:07,784
Big things are gonna happen!
You'll see!

161
00:10:08,035 --> 00:10:09,411
Ross!

162
00:10:09,661 --> 00:10:12,706
You still there?

163
00:10:38,278 --> 00:10:39,571
What are you still doing here?

164
00:10:39,822 --> 00:10:42,658
Just some basic dehydrating
of fruits and vegetables.

165
00:10:42,908 --> 00:10:46,578
Man alive, this thing's fantastic!

166
00:10:46,829 --> 00:10:48,622
Aren't you forgetting anything?

167
00:10:48,872 --> 00:10:50,999
Oh, yeah. I got us a new goldfish.

168
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:53,085
He's feistier than the last one.

169
00:10:53,335 --> 00:10:57,840
Maybe because the last one
was made by Pepperidge Farm.

170
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:01,510
Eddie, isn't there something
you're supposed to be doing now?

171
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:04,138
Not unless it's got something
to do with dehydrating.

172
00:11:04,388 --> 00:11:08,767
Because right now,
I'm a dehydrating maniac!

173
00:11:10,144 --> 00:11:13,397
I thought we had a deal.
I thought by the time I got...

174
00:11:13,647 --> 00:11:15,315
You know what that is?

175
00:11:15,566 --> 00:11:18,485
Your last roommate's kidney?

176
00:11:18,736 --> 00:11:20,487
That's a tomato.

177
00:11:20,738 --> 00:11:25,367
This one definitely goes
in the display.

178
00:11:32,624 --> 00:11:35,711
Hey, Gunther.
Let me get a lemonade to go.

179
00:11:35,961 --> 00:11:37,129
Lemonade?

180
00:11:37,379 --> 00:11:39,548
You okay, man?

181
00:11:39,798 --> 00:11:41,341
It's career stuff.

182
00:11:41,592 --> 00:11:44,386
They killed off
my character on the show.

183
00:11:44,636 --> 00:11:47,181
That's too bad.
How'd they do it?

184
00:11:47,431 --> 00:11:50,309
I fell down an elevator shaft.

185
00:11:50,559 --> 00:11:51,643
That sucks.

186
00:11:51,894 --> 00:11:55,064
I was buried in an avalanche.

187
00:11:55,314 --> 00:11:56,190
What?

188
00:11:56,440 --> 00:12:00,444
I used to be Brice
on <i>All My Children</i>.

189
00:12:20,964 --> 00:12:22,925
Why must everybody watch me sleep?

190
00:12:23,175 --> 00:12:25,344
There'll be no more
watching me sleep! No more...

191
00:12:25,594 --> 00:12:28,180
...watching!

192
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:41,697
I got some great stuff to dehydrate.
Grapes, apricots.

193
00:12:41,947 --> 00:12:45,784
I thought it'd be cool to see
what happens with these water balloons.

194
00:12:46,035 --> 00:12:50,456
Get out.
Get out, get out, get out!

195
00:12:50,664 --> 00:12:52,291
- What?
- You! Move out!

196
00:12:52,541 --> 00:12:56,545
Take your fruit!
Your stupid small fruit and get out!

197
00:12:56,795 --> 00:13:00,257
You want me to move out?

198
00:13:07,306 --> 00:13:13,145
I gotta tell you, that's kind of
out of the blue, don't you think?

199
00:13:13,145 --> 00:13:14,605
This is not out of the blue!

200
00:13:14,855 --> 00:13:18,526
This is smack-dab
in the middle of the blue!

201
00:13:19,527 --> 00:13:21,487
Relax! Take it easy, buddy!

202
00:13:21,737 --> 00:13:24,865
You don't have to tell me twice.

203
00:13:25,241 --> 00:13:28,661
Someone will be by for my stuff.

204
00:13:32,123 --> 00:13:36,585
If you think I'm leaving you
alone with my fish, you're insane!

205
00:13:36,836 --> 00:13:37,837
You want some help?

206
00:13:38,087 --> 00:13:41,549
No help required, <i>chico</i>!

207
00:13:47,376 --> 00:13:48,713
You don't see that everyday.

208
00:13:53,397 --> 00:13:56,734
All the way to the airport, huh?
You know, that's over 30 miles.

209
00:13:56,984 --> 00:14:00,238
That's gonna cost you about so bucks.

210
00:14:00,488 --> 00:14:04,283
Excuse me, that's fifty bucks.

211
00:14:04,659 --> 00:14:07,703
Five-O dollars.

212
00:14:07,954 --> 00:14:11,749
You know what it is?
It's smudgy because they're fax pages.

213
00:14:11,999 --> 00:14:15,711
When I was on <i>Days of our Lives</i>
as Dr. Drake Ramoray...

214
00:14:15,962 --> 00:14:19,382
...they'd send over
the whole script on real paper.

215
00:14:19,632 --> 00:14:21,425
That's great.

216
00:14:21,676 --> 00:14:25,680
If you wanted to expand this scene,
like have the cab crash...

217
00:14:25,930 --> 00:14:27,765
...I could attend to the victims...

218
00:14:28,015 --> 00:14:31,394
...because I have a background
in medical acting.

219
00:14:31,644 --> 00:14:34,188
Okay, listen, thanks for coming in.

220
00:14:34,438 --> 00:14:39,235
Don't thank me for coming in.
At least let me finish.

221
00:14:41,988 --> 00:14:44,198
We could take the expressway...

222
00:14:44,448 --> 00:14:49,245
...but this time of day
you're better off taking the budge.

223
00:14:50,705 --> 00:14:54,333
You were going for bridge there,
weren't you?

224
00:14:54,584 --> 00:14:57,879
I'll have a good day.

225
00:15:00,646 --> 00:15:04,041
Okay, honey, I know you
didn't mean to. I know. Me too.

226
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:08,079
Rach, hang up. You're supposed
to be taking a goddess quiz.

227
00:15:08,121 --> 00:15:09,556
You should lose, like, 100 points...

228
00:15:09,626 --> 00:15:12,351
...just for calling
your boyfriend in the middle of it.

229
00:15:17,924 --> 00:15:19,175
Question number 28.

230
00:15:19,425 --> 00:15:23,888
"Have you ever allowed
a lightning-bearer to take your wind?"

231
00:15:24,138 --> 00:15:27,392
I would have to say no.

232
00:15:28,309 --> 00:15:31,020
And I would have to say...

233
00:15:31,270 --> 00:15:32,146
What?

234
00:15:32,397 --> 00:15:34,065
Do you not remember the puppet guy?

235
00:15:34,315 --> 00:15:40,571
You totally let him wash his feet
in the pool of your inner power.

236
00:15:40,822 --> 00:15:42,573
And his puppet too!

237
00:15:42,824 --> 00:15:44,951
Well, at least
I didn't let some guy...

238
00:15:45,201 --> 00:15:49,622
...into the forest of my righteous
truth on the first date!

239
00:15:52,458 --> 00:15:55,336
- Who?
- Paul!

240
00:15:56,421 --> 00:15:58,756
Moving on, moving on.
Next question.

241
00:15:59,007 --> 00:16:00,466
Okay, number 29.

242
00:16:00,717 --> 00:16:03,636
"Have you ever betrayed
another goddess...

243
00:16:03,886 --> 00:16:06,764
...for a lightning-bearer?"
Okay, number 30.

244
00:16:07,015 --> 00:16:11,436
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Let's go back to 29.

245
00:16:14,022 --> 00:16:17,358
Not to my recollection.

246
00:16:17,608 --> 00:16:19,652
Danny Arshack, ninth grade.

247
00:16:19,902 --> 00:16:22,363
You know the bottle
was pointing at me.

248
00:16:22,613 --> 00:16:26,909
Only because you took up
half the circle!

249
00:16:29,203 --> 00:16:33,082
Listen to you two.
It's so sad.

250
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:37,837
Looks like I'll be going to
the goddess meetings alone.

251
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:40,214
Not when they find out
you slept with Jason Hurley...

252
00:16:40,465 --> 00:16:44,802
...an hour after
he broke up with Monica.

253
00:16:45,301 --> 00:16:46,588
That was only an hour?

254
00:16:46,729 --> 00:16:49,404
You are such a leaf blower!

255
00:16:50,230 --> 00:16:52,739
- Pool drainer!
- Twig snapper!

256
00:16:52,944 --> 00:16:54,078
Monkey butt!

257
00:16:56,715 --> 00:17:00,651
- That is not in the book!
- No, but that's what you are!

258
00:17:13,072 --> 00:17:19,119
Be careful with that 3-D <i>Last Supper</i>.
Judas is a little loose.

259
00:17:22,456 --> 00:17:25,084
Oh, my God! What's going on?

260
00:17:25,334 --> 00:17:28,754
They're taking all my stuff back.
I guess you were right.

261
00:17:29,004 --> 00:17:33,008
No, I wasn't right.
That's what I came here to tell you.

262
00:17:33,258 --> 00:17:36,762
I was totally hung up
on my own stuff the other day.

263
00:17:37,012 --> 00:17:40,766
No, listen. I need the whole
security thing, you know?

264
00:17:41,016 --> 00:17:45,437
To know where my next paycheck is
coming from. But you don't need that.

265
00:17:45,688 --> 00:17:47,231
And that's amazing to me.

266
00:17:47,481 --> 00:17:50,526
I could never do what you do.

267
00:17:50,776 --> 00:17:53,404
- Thanks.
- You hold out for something bigger.

268
00:17:53,654 --> 00:17:55,739
I can't tell you
how much respect I have...

269
00:17:55,990 --> 00:17:58,784
...for you not going
to that stupid audition.

270
00:17:59,034 --> 00:18:01,161
- I went.
- Great! How did it go?

271
00:18:01,412 --> 00:18:03,247
- I didn't get it.
- Good for you!

272
00:18:03,497 --> 00:18:06,250
You're living the dream!

273
00:18:06,542 --> 00:18:09,295
All right, then!

274
00:18:09,545 --> 00:18:12,089
Not my parrot.

275
00:18:12,339 --> 00:18:15,342
I can't watch this.

276
00:18:15,593 --> 00:18:17,803
Hey, hold on, hold on.

277
00:18:18,053 --> 00:18:21,807
How much for the...
How much to save the bird?

278
00:18:22,057 --> 00:18:23,767
- Twelve hundred.
- Dollars?

279
00:18:24,018 --> 00:18:26,854
You spent $1200 on a plastic bird?

280
00:18:27,104 --> 00:18:29,940
It was an impulse buy.
Near the register.

281
00:18:30,190 --> 00:18:32,568
Go ahead with the bird.

282
00:18:32,818 --> 00:18:37,615
Do you have anything for around $200?

283
00:18:37,656 --> 00:18:40,492
The dog.

284
00:18:43,203 --> 00:18:44,371
I'll take it.

285
00:18:44,622 --> 00:18:47,833
My gift to you, man.

286
00:18:48,751 --> 00:18:49,919
Thanks, Ross!

287
00:18:50,169 --> 00:18:52,588
I really liked that bird, though.

288
00:18:52,838 --> 00:18:56,091
But the dog!

289
00:19:03,974 --> 00:19:05,309
Here are your cakes.

290
00:19:05,559 --> 00:19:07,186
We didn't order cake.

291
00:19:07,436 --> 00:19:10,773
No, I know. They're from me.

292
00:19:11,023 --> 00:19:12,650
You guys, this is not good.

293
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:15,361
We have enough trouble
with guys stealing our wind...

294
00:19:15,611 --> 00:19:18,197
...without taking it from each other.

295
00:19:18,447 --> 00:19:20,407
You're right.

296
00:19:20,658 --> 00:19:23,744
I love you goddesses.

297
00:19:24,995 --> 00:19:28,290
I don't ever want
to suck your wind again.

298
00:19:28,540 --> 00:19:30,960
- Thank you. So are we good?
- We're good.

299
00:19:31,210 --> 00:19:32,878
We're good?

300
00:19:33,128 --> 00:19:37,550
Let me take these back.
They'll take it out of my paycheck.

301
00:19:39,218 --> 00:19:42,805
Ding-dong, the psycho's gone!

302
00:19:45,891 --> 00:19:47,476
Are you sure this time?

303
00:19:47,726 --> 00:19:49,645
I actually saw him leave.

304
00:19:49,895 --> 00:19:52,523
That guy is holding a human head.

305
00:19:52,773 --> 00:19:56,610
He's holding a human head!

306
00:19:57,570 --> 00:19:58,612
Check it out, man!

307
00:19:58,862 --> 00:20:01,824
I tore it off a mannequin
in the alley behind Macy's.

308
00:20:02,074 --> 00:20:03,158
There's no alley behind Macy's.

309
00:20:03,409 --> 00:20:06,161
So I got it in the junior miss
department. Big diff.

310
00:20:06,412 --> 00:20:10,040
It'll make a hell of a conversation
piece at our next cocktail party.

311
00:20:10,291 --> 00:20:13,502
"Our next cocktail party"?

312
00:20:13,752 --> 00:20:18,132
We'll put chips in it.
We'll make it a chip chick.

313
00:20:19,842 --> 00:20:21,886
Do you remember yesterday?

314
00:20:22,136 --> 00:20:25,806
Yes, I think I vaguely recall it.

315
00:20:29,351 --> 00:20:34,023
Do you remember
talking to me yesterday?

316
00:20:39,069 --> 00:20:40,196
So what happened?

317
00:20:40,446 --> 00:20:42,364
We took a road trip to Las Vegas!

318
00:20:42,615 --> 00:20:46,076
Oh, sweet Moses!

319
00:20:46,118 --> 00:20:48,704
So on this road trip,
did you win any money?

320
00:20:48,954 --> 00:20:52,124
I crapped out. But Mr. 21 here!
He cleans up!

321
00:20:52,374 --> 00:20:54,960
$300! He buys me these new shoes.

322
00:20:55,211 --> 00:20:56,337
Nice.

323
00:20:56,587 --> 00:21:00,174
See you upstairs. See you, pals!

324
00:21:02,593 --> 00:21:07,306
Is anyone else starting
to really like him?

325
00:21:25,491 --> 00:21:27,952
May I help you?

326
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:31,247
Why doesn't my key work,
and what's my stuff doing downstairs?

327
00:21:31,497 --> 00:21:34,542
I'm sorry.

328
00:21:34,583 --> 00:21:35,876
Have we met?

329
00:21:36,126 --> 00:21:39,171
It's Eddie, you freak!
Your roommate.

330
00:21:39,421 --> 00:21:41,465
I'm sorry...

331
00:21:41,715 --> 00:21:45,511
...I already have a roommate.

332
00:21:51,058 --> 00:21:57,064
He's lived here for years.
I don't know what you're talking about.

333
00:21:58,232 --> 00:22:02,987
No, he moved out and I moved in.

334
00:22:03,237 --> 00:22:06,657
Well, I think we'd remember
something like that.

335
00:22:06,907 --> 00:22:09,702
I know I would.

336
00:22:09,952 --> 00:22:12,288
That's a good point.

337
00:22:12,538 --> 00:22:13,581
Okay, wow.

338
00:22:13,831 --> 00:22:17,626
I guess I got the wrong apartment.

339
00:22:19,211 --> 00:22:21,547
- I'm terribly sorry.
- Hey, no problem.

340
00:22:21,797 --> 00:22:24,508
See you.

341
00:22:29,305 --> 00:22:34,059
Goodbye, you fruit-drying psychopath.

342
00:22:34,310 --> 00:22:38,147
- You want me to help you unpack?
- Nah, I'm okay.

343
00:22:38,397 --> 00:22:42,026
Just so you know, I'm not
moving back in because I have to.

344
00:22:42,276 --> 00:22:44,987
I mean, I do have to, but...

345
00:22:45,237 --> 00:22:48,365
It's just that that place,
it wasn't really...

346
00:22:48,616 --> 00:22:51,494
I mean, this is...

347
00:22:51,744 --> 00:22:54,830
Welcome home, man.

348
00:23:02,755 --> 00:23:06,759
- A little foos?
- Absolutely!

349
00:23:07,843 --> 00:23:10,096
What happened to the foosball?

350
00:23:10,346 --> 00:23:13,307
It's a cantaloupe.

351
00:23:16,778 --> 00:23:19,614
Are we gonna bring this out
every time Ross comes over?

352
00:23:19,864 --> 00:23:23,576
He paid a lot of money for it.

353
00:23:28,164 --> 00:23:31,459
I'm gonna hold him a different way.

354
00:23:31,710 --> 00:23:35,255
If you hated it so much,
why'd you buy it in the first place?

355
00:23:35,505 --> 00:23:39,259
Well, I had a whole ceramic
zoo thing going over there.

356
00:23:39,509 --> 00:23:42,367
But without the other ones,
it looks tacky.

357
00:23:42,422 --> 00:23:44,867
Yeah, with things like this,
more is always better.

358
00:23:47,871 --> 00:23:52,167
Is he housetrained or will he leave
little bathroom tiles all over?

359
00:23:52,417 --> 00:23:54,961
Stay.

360
00:23:55,253 --> 00:23:56,504
Stay!

361
00:23:56,755 --> 00:24:00,175
Good fake dog.
